tree.getiterator - update for Python 3.9+

This PR provides the needed changes.

commit.message: Added keyboard shortcuts to README.md

Misc updates 2020

- Disabled check for updates on launch. Also removed this option from the
menu
- Fixed issue where user chooses to quit, then save, then cancels
(previously this would have continued quitting, potentially resulting in
data loss. Now if saving is cancelled, the quit operation is cancelled)
- HighlightJS now local (MathJax needs to be made local too)
- Added dialog to add tables

commit.message: Fixing copy to clipboard  for Webkit2 WebView
Webkit2 needs package gir1.2-webkit2-4.0

Fixing zooming in/out

Webkit2 does not know zoom_out/in functions.
We have to use set_zoom_level now.

Upgrading to Webkit2

On Ubuntu 19.10 Webkit is no longer available.
The package is now gir1.2-webkit2-4.0.
So I upgraded RemarkableWindow to use webkit2.

Note: not sure if there's a equal line to console-message.
I have not seen any distracting messages in the console.
So I removed that line.

Adding basic snapcraft.yaml

Adding seding of Popen calls which works
According to the solution from @jamesh
at https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/confine-python-popen-child-to-snap-container/13955/4

Removing hardcoded executable paths

Instead of using hardcoded "remarkable" execution,
get the actual execution name from the system (argv0).
Fixes https://github.com/jamiemcg/Remarkable/issues/315
Fix: Hide findbar properly when escape key is pressed. Still problem: matched text remains highlighted after findbar is hidden
Fix menu labels
